'''Joost Augusteijn''' (born 24 July 1960, [[Amsterdam]])<ref name=uva>[http://www.albumacademicum.uva.nl/cgi/b/bib/bib-idx?type=simple;lang=nl;c=ap;rgn1=entirerecord;q1=augusteijn;x=0;y=0;cc=ap;view=reslist;sort=achternaam;fmt=long;page=reslist;start=1;size=1 J. Augusteijn, 1960 -] at the UvA Album Academicum</ref> is a Dutch historian and lecturer. He was formerly a lecturer in Modern Irish History at [[Trinity College Dublin]] and [[Queen's University Belfast]]. He currently is an Associate professor of European History at [[Leiden University]]<ref name=leid>[https://www.universiteitleiden.nl/en/staffmembers/joost-augusteijn#tab-1 Faculty page at Leiden University]</ref>
Augusteijn earned his PhD at the [[University of Amsterdam]] on the history of the [[Irish Republican Army]].<ref name=uva/><ref name=leid/> He has written many books including 'Patrick Pearse: The Making of a Revolutionary' and 'The Irish Revolution'.<ref>[http://www.historyireland.com/20th-century-contemporary-history/patrick-pearseproto-fascist-eccentric-or-mainstream-european-thinker/ Patrick Pearse:proto-fascist eccentric or mainstream European thinker?] at historyireland.com</ref>
